content.description: Moving from the beginning moves into the face.
content.location: Directly to the right of "Easier of the face climbs". Climb has a start a few feet to the right, with small holds into the face with very small feet, move directly up to the left of a large ledge and over the small protrusion into the small corner with the same finish as the route to the left.

content.description: First ~crux is pulling onto the ledge under the top-out. After a committing pull into the corner nearing the top-out. The second ~crux is just under the top-out, somewhat glassy corner with high feet to a mantle.
content.location: Directly to the right of "Corner under the bridge". Has a different start including the face. Starting on smaller holds, further left close to the corner, then directly up the left side of the first face then to the right of the tree. pulling into the crux, into the corner then to the mantle.

content.description: First crux is the small dyno out of the corner. Second being the move up onto large ledge pulling through the off-width.
content.location: Route starts about 20 feet from "Harder of the face climbs". It is under the second bridge. One large recognizable feature is the old bolt about 15 feet off the ground (not good protection). Start in the large rattley hand sized crack, continue up the rattley crack, taking advantage of the left face of the corner, past the old bolt and start looking right to the right face of the corner. Small right hand to the committing dyno jug on the corner of the outside face. Pull up onto the small ledge with a nice undercling rest. Traverse back into the now off-width crack up onto the large ledge. then up the slightly over-vertical face to lip. Lower off.

content.description: Only possible crux could be if the TR is set up so that it lays left of the tree half-way up the pitch. Can be dirty rock, good idea to rap first with a brush.
content.location: (under the first bridge) Start beside the tree at the base of the block-y corner the route lays directly up the corner with large stair steps all the way to the rim. Climber has opportunity to top-out.

content.description: Usually quite cool in summer, with leaves on the trees, and out of the sun (can be very wet if any rain lately). Later in the year with no leaves on the tree, plenty of sun still decent conditions throughout the year. Rock can be quite dirty, and is usually worth a rap to check routes and scrub holds before climbing.
